snippet.textDisplay:
First: The song gave me chills. I love it. I then saw the name and it took me to another level. Memento Mori: “Remember you must die.” The point of this reminder isn’t to be morbid or promote fear, but to inspire, motivate and clarify. The idea has been central to art, philosophy, literature, architecture, and more throughout history. From the Roman's.

For my sisters and brothers reading these comments looking into this song deeper, look into Stocism. Not a religion, but a practice of how to live one's life, without fear. I suspect this song and these times just may have been inspired by it.

P.s. Plug for https://dailystoic.com/ borrowed part of my explanation above. Ryan Holiday is an awesome modern-day practicing Stoic with multiple published books.
